Telecom Churn - Ensemble Technique Project¶

Domain:¶

  • Telecom

Context:¶

  • A telecom company wants to use their historical customer data to predict behaviour to retain customers. You can analyse all relevant customer data and develop focused customer retention programs.

Attribute Information:¶

  • CustomerID: This column is a unique identifier for each row. It helps to identify each client of the telecom company.
  • gender: The sex of the person. Male or Female.
  • SeniorCitizen: If the person falls in the senior citizen category or no. 1 being yes and 0 being a no
  • Partner: If the client has a partner. A husband or a wife, or just a partner also.
  • Dependents: If the client has any dependents, like children, old parents and grandparents. Basically those who do not earn in the family.
  • tenure: For how long the client has used the telecom service.
  • PhoneService: Does the client has the phone service - yes or no .
  • MultipleLines: Does the client have multiple lines service - yes or no or no such service exist.
  • InternetService: Does the client have internet service - yes or no or no such service exist.
  • OnlineSecurity: Does the client have online security service - yes or no or no such service exist.
  • OnlineBackup: Does the client have online backup service - yes or no or no such service exist.
  • DeviceProtection: Does the client have Device Protection service - yes or no or no such service exist.
  • TechSupport: Does the client have Technical Support service - yes or no or no such service exist.
  • StreamingTV: Does the client have Television Streaming service - yes or no or no such service exist.
  • StreamingMovies: Does the client have Movies Streaming service - yes or no or no such service exist.
  • Contract: How does the client pay the bill? Monthly, once in a year or one in two years
  • PaperlessBilling: Does the client use paperless billing - yes or no
  • PaymentMethod: How does the client pay the bill? via electronic check, mail check, bank transfer (automatic), credit card (automatic)
  • MonthlyCharges: How much does the client bill comes out to be on a monthly basis.
  • TotalCharges: How much does the client pay (incl. taxes)
  • Churn: Customers who left within the last month

Learning Outcomes:¶

  • EDA.
  • Splitiing Datasets into Training and Testing set.
  • Bulding Models.
  • Comparing Models based on their accuracy. precision, recall and F1-score.
  • Pickle-ing the model.
  • Making a GUI for the model.

Lets Now replace the categorical values to numbers. Machine Learning models learn from numbers quickly.¶

In [14]:
cat_cols = {'gender': {'Female': 1, 'Male': 0},
           'Partner': {'Yes': 1, 'No': 0},
           'Dependents': {'Yes': 1, 'No': 0},
           'PhoneService': {'Yes': 1, 'No': 0},
           'MultipleLines': {'No phone service': -1, 'No': 0, 'Yes': 1},
           'InternetService': {'DSL': 0, 'Fiber optic': 1, 'No': 2},
           'OnlineSecurity': {'No': 0, 'Yes': 1, 'No internet service': -1},
           'OnlineBackup': {'No': 0, 'Yes': 1, 'No internet service': -1},
           'DeviceProtection': {'No': 0, 'Yes': 1, 'No internet service': -1},
           'TechSupport': {'No': 0, 'Yes': 1, 'No internet service': -1},
           'StreamingTV': {'No': 0, 'Yes': 1, 'No internet service': -1},
           'StreamingMovies': {'No': 0, 'Yes': 1, 'No internet service': -1},
           'Contract': {'Month-to-month': 0, 'One year': 1, 'Two year': 2},
           'PaperlessBilling': {'Yes': 1, 'No': 0},
           'PaymentMethod': {'Electronic check': 1,'Mailed check':2,'Bank transfer (automatic)':3,'Credit card (automatic)':4},
           'Churn': {'Yes': 1, 'No': 0}}
churn = churn.replace(cat_cols)

Scaling the feature columns to make it easier to calculation the precision, recall and the F-1 score.¶

In [40]:
from sklearn.preprocessing import RobustScaler
X = churn.drop(['Churn'], axis = 1)
y = churn['Churn']

# Applying RobustScaler to make it less prone to outliers
features = X.columns
scaler = RobustScaler()
X = pd.DataFrame(scaler.fit_transform(X), columns = features)

# Scaling the independent variables
Xs = X.apply(zscore)

display(X.shape, Xs.shape, y.shape)
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size = 0.3, random_state = 42)

Logistic Regression¶

In [41]:
LR = LogisticRegression(solver="liblinear")
model_lr = LR.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_pred = LR.predict(X_test)

accuracy_ = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
precision_lr = precision_score(y_test, y_pred)
recall_lr = recall_score(y_test, y_pred)
f1_score_lr = 2 * (precision_lr * recall_lr) / (precision_lr + recall_lr)
print('Training Score: ', LR.score(X_train, y_train).round(3))
print('Test Score: ', LR.score(X_test, y_test).round(3))
print('Precision Score: ', precision_lr.round(3))
print('Recall Score: ', recall_lr.round(3))
print('f1 Score: ', f1_score_lr.round(3))

df = pd.DataFrame([accuracy_.round(3), precision_lr.round(3), recall_lr.round(3), f1_score_lr.round(3)], 
                  columns = ['Logistic Regression Model']).T
df.columns = ['Accuracy', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'f1']

From the above dataframe, we can see that SVM has give the maximum accruracy of 79.3%, precision of 65.2%(measure if relevant data points), recall of 47.4%(True Positive Rate).¶

We will be using SVM to predict the target because:¶

  • SVM works relatively well when there is a clear margin of separation between classes.
  • SVM is more effective in high dimensional spaces.(20 columns).
  • SVM is relatively memory efficient.
  • A small change to the data does not greatly affect the hyperplane and hence the SVM. So the SVM model is stable.
  • SVM can efficiently handle non-linear data using Kernel trick.

def submit_action():

    import pandas as pd
    churn_predict = pd.DataFrame(columns=['gender', 'SeniorCitizen', 'Partner', 'Dependents', 'tenure', 'PhoneService',
                                         'MultipleLines', 'InternetService', 'OnlineSecurity', 'OnlineBackup',
                                         'DeviceProtection', 'TechSupport', 'StreamingTV', 'StreamingMovies', 'Contract',
                                         'PaperlessBilling', 'PaymentMethod', 'MonthlyCharges', 'TotalCharges'])
    
    churn_predict.loc[0,'gender'] = g.get()
    churn_predict.loc[0,'SeniorCitizen'] = sen_cit.get()
    churn_predict.loc[0,'Partner'] = p.get()
    churn_predict.loc[0,'Dependents'] = dep.get()
    churn_predict.loc[0,'tenure'] = ten.get()
    churn_predict.loc[0,'PhoneService'] = ps.get()
    churn_predict.loc[0,'MultipleLines'] = ml.get()
    churn_predict.loc[0,'InternetService'] = int_serv.get()
    churn_predict.loc[0,'OnlineSecurity'] = on_sec.get()
    churn_predict.loc[0,'OnlineBackup'] = ob.get()
    churn_predict.loc[0,'DeviceProtection'] = dp.get()
    churn_predict.loc[0,'TechSupport'] = ts.get()
    churn_predict.loc[0,'StreamingTV'] = stv.get()

    churn_predict.loc[0,'Contract'] = con.get()

def prediction_action():
    sv_model=pickle.loads(selected_model)
    output = sv_model.predict(DB)
    if output == 1:
        result = 'Churn'
    elif output == 0:
        result = 'Not Churn'
    Predict_entrybox=ttk.Entry(window,width=16)
    Predict_entrybox.grid(row=27,column=1)
    Predict_entrybox.insert(1,str(result))
    
Predict_button=ttk.Button(window,text="Predict",command=prediction_action)
